oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of the U.S.S. Housatonic
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The U.S.S. Housatonic was a mine layer in World War I. This ship layed 9339 mines and survived the war. Guy E. Housholder of Knoxville enlisted at age 18 and served Fireman 2nd Class. He was honorably discharged as an Engineman 2nd Class on August 32, 1919. After the war, he worked as a machinist for the railroad, and died in 1961.
